    <h2>Commercial restaurant grills are different equipment from residential outdoor BBQ.</h2>

    <p>Vulcan VCCB-25, Garland MGM-24, MagiKitch'n MK-30 (Wolf Industrial commercial line, separate from residential Wolf cooking), Imperial IRB-24, Star Ultra-Max: these are heavy-duty cooking equipment built for restaurant kitchens. 12 to 16 hour service days, continuous high-heat operation, 30,000 to 50,000 BTU per burner, gas connections sized 1-inch minimum (residential is 1/2-inch). LA restaurants depend on these workhorses to produce the steaks, burgers, and grilled proteins your business runs on.</p>

    <p>If you're looking for <strong>outdoor patio grill repair</strong> (Lynx, Fire Magic, Twin Eagles, Wolf Outdoor: residential built-in BBQ), see our <a href="/outdoor/grill-repair/">outdoor grill repair page</a>. <strong>This page covers commercial restaurant grills only.</strong></p>

    <p>Our techs service the full commercial grill lineup across LA County, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. <strong>Vulcan VCCB Series</strong> (24, 25, 36, 47, 60-inch radiant gas char-broilers, the most common LA commercial grill). <strong>Garland MGM Master Series</strong> (MGM24, MGM36, MGM48). <strong>MagiKitch'n MK Series</strong> (MK24, MK36, premium institutional). <strong>Imperial IRB Series</strong>. <strong>Star Ultra-Max</strong> (mid-range). <strong>Keating Miraclean</strong>. <strong>Bakers Pride</strong> XX series.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong> license. <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410</strong>. <strong>CSLB C-20 HVAC</strong> scope for adjacent commercial gas and refrigeration work. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent context: <a href="/commercial/">commercial appliance repair</a>.</p>
